title: Robert Ludlum (Bourne 04) - The Bourne Legacy
description:
Jason Bourne, international assassin of deadly repute, was an identity 
assumed by covert agent David Webb. Retired from the CIA and now a professor 
at Georgetown University, Webb's life is finally his own--until he becomes 
the target of an assassin and is framed for the murder of his two closest 
associates. Fighting for his life against unseen assailants, the Bourne 
identity asserts itself, leaving Jason Bourne in control. Barely a half-step 
ahead of his nemesis and the CIA, who believes he has gone rogue, Bourne 
finds himself a pawn in a larger, far deadlier game
